Reasoning: The paper deals with the secrecy capacity of wiretap channels, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR). The use of correlated random coding and the analysis of the continuity of the secrecy capacity suggest that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-categories of signal processing (cs.SI) and multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the use of an auxiliary channel and the consideration of the sender-eavesdropper communication suggest that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-category of networking and internet architecture (cs.NI).
